"<div class=\"announce instapaper_body md\" data-path=\"README.md\" id=\"file\"><article class=\"markdown-body entry-content\" itemprop=\"text\"><p><a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/gaggle/assert-dir\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/10703466128dc33b7ceb2406b20fc50daeeab343/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f676167676c652f6173736572742d6469722e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572\" alt=\"Build Status\" data-canonical-src=\"https://travis-ci.org/gaggle/assert-dir.svg?branch=master\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></a></p>\n<h1><a href=\"#assert-dir\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\" id=\"user-content-assert-dir\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>assert-dir</h1>\n<p>Asynchronous assertion of two folders being identical</p>\n<p>Supports custom comparers for file globs,\nso you can assert specific formats are semantically identical\neven if their literal content differs.\n(e.g. HTML or XML files can differ in linebreaks without being semantically different)</p>\n<h2><a href=\"#installation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\" id=\"user-content-installation\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Installation</h2>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell\"><pre>npm i gaggle/assert-dir --save-dev</pre></div>\n<h2><a href=\"#use\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\" id=\"user-content-use\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Use</h2>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-js\"><pre><span class=\"pl-k\">const</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">assertDir</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">require</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>assert-dir<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>)\n\n<span class=\"pl-en\">assertDir</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>path1<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>, <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>path2<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>)</pre></div>\n<p>Custom comparers are passed in as an array,\neach element a two-element array\nconsisting of a pattern and a compare-function.</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-js\"><pre><span class=\"pl-k\">const</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">allFilesAreGood</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> [<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>*<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>, () <span class=\"pl-k\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">true</span>]\n<span class=\"pl-en\">assertDir</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>path1<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>, <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>path2<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>, [allFilesAreGood])</pre></div>\n<p>Multiple custom comparers can be added,\nfiles are matched in order.</p>\n<p>A compare-function is a synchronous function\nthat returns false if the two files are not identical.\nIt is passed these arguments:</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;relative path&gt;, &lt;actual path&gt;, &lt;expected path&gt;, &lt;actual data&gt;, &lt;expected data&gt;\n</code></pre>\n</article></div>"